@ossified E7-OSS-05 FALLBACK_TRIGGER_ON_NONZERO_RC_NOT_ONLY_EXCEPTION subprocess fallback must fire when rc != 0 AND rc != 2 (not only Python exception). Hexa binary can fail internally (GLIBC mismatch / input parse error / runtime panic) with rc=1 while subprocess itself returns normally. Current logic: `except Exception` only catches OSError (binary absent). Patch needed: explicit `if rc not in (0, 2): use_fallback()`.
@ossified E7-OSS-06 FRESH_LORA_CONST_LR_2E-6_INSUFFICIENT_ON_95MB with const LR 2e-6 + batch=8 seq=1024 + fresh LoRA r=32, 14B model collapses to single-byte repeat by step 63 on mixed stripped+kowiki 95MB corpus. Loss drops 4.73→0.94 in 63 steps is memorization-collapse, not convergence. Root: corpus too small for 14B capacity × LoRA r=32 × low LR = model finds trivial local minimum (most-common-byte repeat). Fix path A: LR up (5e-6/1e-5 with warmup). Fix path B: corpus 10× scale (P22 full 1GB+ ingest). Fix path C: skip LoRA training, use BASE Qwen2.5-14B-Instruct + prompt eng for persona.

@path_pivot 도착지1(페르소나) 최단경로 — LoRA 수렴 대신 base Qwen2.5-14B-Instruct serve + serving/hire_routes.hexa real LLM wire. Φ probe 는 base forward 시 computed (학습 불필요). Details in new convergence: persona_base_serve.convergence (TBD).

@root_cause_1 inline_collapse_score ASCII-only: ch*10 check covers ['n',' ','?',"'"] only — Korean byte/char repeats (녕×N, 낙×N w/ spaces) NOT detected. kr_gen_sentinel.hexa has correct byte-level max_byte_run but is NOT called from r10 inline python.
@root_cause_2 f1_watchdog dead_pid false_training: reports TRAINING after process death — watchdog heartbeat check missing PID liveness probe.
@root_cause_3 loss_0.41_at_step_200_was_collapse_not_convergence — same pattern as r9 unnoticed. stripped corpus + const LR + fresh LoRA alone insufficient; requires corpus diversity (kowiki mix) + seed sweep + sentinel w/ non-ASCII coverage.

@ossified E7-OSS-01 INLINE_PY_COLLAPSE_SCORE_ASCII_ONLY never rely on inline ch*10 for non-ASCII. Call kr_gen_sentinel.hexa subprocess (exit code authoritative) OR replicate max_byte_run semantics (byte-level any-byte repeat detection).
@ossified E7-OSS-02 WATCHDOG_PID_LIVENESS_MISSING file-status 'TRAINING' line must be invalidated by kill -0 PID check before report. PATCHED 2026-04-18 in training/deploy/alm14b_r10_watcher.hexa (pid_alive() gate + TRAIN_PID env + pgrep fallback + DEAD_PID override).
@ossified E7-OSS-03 LOSS_BELOW_1.0_AT_EARLY_STEP_SUSPECT_COLLAPSE loss sub-1.0 at step<500 on 14B LoRA fresh-init requires kr_gen_sentinel PASS before accepting as convergence. VERIFIED FIRING 2026-04-18 r10c_attempt_4 step=63 loss=0.9515 — gate worked.
@ossified E7-OSS-04 UNSLOTH_FAST_GENERATE_KWARG_BLEED unsloth fast_generate injects num_logits_to_keep into kwargs which transformers >=5.0 _validate_model_kwargs rejects with ValueError. Bypass: use manual greedy loop — model(input_ids=g_seq).logits[:,-1,:].argmax — instead of model.generate(). R10 attempt_1 hit the SAME kwarg in FORWARD path (fixed by E5 rename); attempt_4 hit it in GENERATE path (fixed by bypass). Root cause pattern: unsloth maintains its own kwarg list that lags transformers API changes.

